<item>
            <title>[GROOVY-3833] AST Browser doesn&apos;t use same classloader as groovyConsole. loaded JARs aren&apos;t found in AST Browser</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-3833</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The GroovyConsole AST browser doesn&apos;t use the same classloader for the AST BRowser. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;1. Open groovyConsole and import a JAR using the Script menu item. &lt;br/&gt;
2. Write a script that uses something out of that JAR&lt;br/&gt;
3. Open AST Browser&lt;br/&gt;
4. AST browser will show a ClassNodeFOund exception for anything out of the JAR&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I suspect that the classes are being loaded into the classloader GroovyConsole uses to execute the script but not the classloader used to execute AST Browser. &lt;/p&gt;</description>
